## 🗄️ Database Schema

### 1. `purchase_orders` Table

**Purpose**: Standalone purchase order management with vendor portal integration

#### Schema Definition

```sql
CREATE TABLE public.purchase_orders (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    po_number INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- Auto-incremented via sequence
    requester_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES profiles(id),
    project_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES projects(id),
    
    -- Vendor Information
    vendor_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    vendor_bank_details TEXT NOT NULL,
    vendor_upi TEXT,
    
    -- Order Details
    item_description TEXT NOT NULL,
    quantity INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
    unit_price NUMERIC NOT NULL,
    total_amount NUMERIC NOT NULL,
    
    -- Documents
    cost_comparison_url TEXT NOT NULL,
    po_document_url TEXT NOT NULL,
    
    -- Approval Workflow
    status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',
    admin_approved_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    admin_approved_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    admin_rejection_reason TEXT,
    ceo_approved_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    ceo_approved_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    ceo_hold_reason TEXT,
    
    -- Vendor Portal Fields (Extended)
    vendor_access_token TEXT,
    delivery_status TEXT,
    lr_number TEXT,
    transporter_name TEXT,
    dispatch_date DATE,
    vendor_invoice_url TEXT,
    
    -- System Fields
    linked_payment_id UUID,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### Status Values

| Status | Description | Next Action |
|--------|-------------|-------------|
| `pending` | Newly submitted | Admin review |
| `admin_approved` | Admin verified | CEO approval |
| `ceo_approved` | Final approval | Payment creation |
| `rejected` | Admin rejected | Requester resubmit |
| `ceo_hold` | CEO on hold | Awaiting clarification |

#### Indexes

```sql
CREATE INDEX idx_purchase_orders_project ON purchase_orders(project_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_purchase_orders_status ON purchase_orders(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_purchase_orders_po_number ON purchase_orders(po_number);
```

---

### 2. `material_requests` Table

**Purpose**: BOQ-driven material procurement with integrated quote comparison

#### Schema Definition

```sql
CREATE TABLE material_requests (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    project_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES projects(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    phase_id UUID REFERENCES project_phases(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
    requested_by UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES profiles(id),
    
    -- Request Details
    boq_items JSONB DEFAULT '[]'::jsonb,
    urgency TEXT DEFAULT 'normal' 
        CHECK (urgency IN ('low', 'normal', 'high', 'critical')),
    notes TEXT,
    
    -- Workflow Status
    status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending' 
        CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'sourcing', 'quoted', 'approved', 
                         'ordered', 'delivered', 'cancelled')),
    
    -- Delivery Tracking (Granular)
    order_status TEXT 
        CHECK (order_status IN ('ordered', 'loading', 'shipped', 
                                'unloading', 'delivered')),
    
    -- Assignment & Approval
    assigned_to_purchase UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    selected_quote_id UUID REFERENCES vendor_quotes(id),
    approval_status TEXT 
        CHECK (approval_status IN ('pending', 'pending_boi', 
                                   'boi_approved', 'pending_admin',
                                   'admin_approved', 'pending_ceo',
                                   'ceo_approved', 'rejected')),
    
    -- Approval Chain
    boi_approved_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    boi_approved_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    admin_approved_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    admin_approved_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    ceo_approved_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    ceo_approved_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    rejection_reason TEXT,
    
    -- System Fields
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### BOQ Items JSON Structure

```typescript
interface BOQItem {
  boq_id: string;           // Reference to project_boq.id
  material_name: string;
  quantity: number;
  unit: string;
  estimated_rate?: number;
  total_estimated?: number;
  urgent?: boolean;
}
```

#### Workflow State Machine

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> pending: Engineer creates request
    pending --> sourcing: Purchase assigns
    sourcing --> quoted: Quotes added (min 3)
    quoted --> approved: Quote selected
    approved --> ordered: Order placed
    ordered --> delivered: Delivery complete
    
    pending --> cancelled
    sourcing --> cancelled
    quoted --> cancelled
    
    note right of quoted: Multi-vendor comparison
    note right of approved: 3-tier approval (BOI→Admin→CEO)
```

---

### 3. `vendor_quotes` Table

**Purpose**: Multi-vendor price comparison for material requests

#### Schema Definition

```sql
CREATE TABLE vendor_quotes (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    material_request_id UUID REFERENCES material_requests(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    boq_item_id UUID REFERENCES project_boq(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    project_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES projects(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    
    -- Vendor Details
    vendor_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    vendor_contact TEXT,
    vendor_email TEXT,
    vendor_bank_name TEXT,
    vendor_account_number TEXT,
    vendor_ifsc TEXT,
    vendor_gst TEXT,
    
    -- Quote Details
    quoted_unit_price NUMERIC NOT NULL,
    quoted_total NUMERIC NOT NULL,
    quoted_items JSONB DEFAULT '[]'::jsonb,  -- Array of QuotedItem
    
    -- Quote Metadata
    quote_document_url TEXT,
    quote_drive_link TEXT,
    validity_date DATE,
    delivery_days INTEGER,
    is_selected BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
    notes TEXT,
    
    -- System Fields
    created_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### Quoted Items JSON Structure

```typescript
interface QuotedItem {
  material_name: string;
  quantity: number;
  unit: string;
  unit_price: number;
  total: number;
}
```

---

### 4. `purchase_progress_logs` Table

**Purpose**: Granular tracking of procurement updates

#### Schema Definition

```sql
CREATE TABLE purchase_progress_logs (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    material_request_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES material_requests(id),
    update_text TEXT NOT NULL,
    status_update TEXT,  -- Optional status change
    updated_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    updated_by_name TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### Common Update Examples

- "Contacted Vendor ABC, waiting for quote"
- "Quote received from XYZ - ₹45,000 for 500 units"
- "Material loaded at warehouse - LR #12345"
- "Dispatched via ABC Logistics - ETA 2 days"

---

### 5. `procurement_timeline` Table

**Purpose**: Audit trail for all procurement actions

#### Schema Definition

```sql
CREATE TABLE procurement_timeline (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    material_request_id UUID REFERENCES material_requests(id),
    action TEXT NOT NULL,  -- 'created', 'quote_added', 'approved', etc.
    performed_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
    performed_by_name TEXT,
    details JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

