### Workflow 3: Vendor Portal (External Access)

#### Purpose

Allow external vendors to:
- View PO details (read-only)
- Update dispatch status
- Upload invoices
- No authentication required (token-based access)

#### Access Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Admin
    participant S as System
    participant V as Vendor
    participant DB as Database
    
    A->>S: Create Purchase Order
    S->>DB: Generate vendor_access_token
    S->>V: Email with Portal Link
    Note over V: Link: /vendor-portal/{token}
    
    V->>S: Open Portal (No Login)
    S->>DB: Validate Token
    alt Token Valid
        DB->>S: Return PO Details
        S->>V: Display PO
        V->>S: Update Dispatch Status
        V->>S: Upload Invoice
        S->>DB: Update PO
        DB->>A: Notify Admin
    else Token Invalid
        S->>V: Error: Invalid Access
    end
```

#### Vendor Portal UI Components

**File**: [src/pages/public/VendorPortalPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/hp/Desktop/igochain-main/src/pages/public/VendorPortalPage.tsx)

##### Key Features

1. **Token Validation**: URL-based access (no password)
2. **PO Details Display**: Read-only project & order info
3. **Dispatch Update Form**:
   - LR Number
   - Transporter Name
   - Dispatch Date
4. **Invoice Upload**: Direct to Supabase Storage
5. **Status Tracking**: Visual timeline

##### Vendor Actions

```typescript
// 1. Mark as Dispatched
const handleMarkDispatched = async () => {
  await supabase
    .from('purchase_orders')
    .update({
      delivery_status: 'DISPATCHED',
      lr_number: lrNumber,
      transporter_name: transporter,
      dispatch_date: dispatchDate
    })
    .eq('vendor_access_token', token);
  
  // Sends real-time notification to purchase team
};

// 2. Upload Invoice
const handleUploadInvoice = async (file: File) => {
  // Upload to Supabase Storage
  const { data, error } = await supabase.storage
    .from('vendor-invoices')
    .upload(`${poId}/${file.name}`, file);
  
  // Update PO with invoice URL
  await supabase
    .from('purchase_orders')
    .update({ vendor_invoice_url: data.path })
    .eq('vendor_access_token', token);
};
```

